section.def:
animal (動物) includes any
            mammal, bird, reptile, amphibian, fish or any other vertebrate or invertebrate, whether
            wild or tame;

election (選舉) means an
            ordinary election or a by-election held under the Election Regulation;
                (Added 6 of 2015 s. 3)

medical and health professional (醫療專業人員) means a medical practitioner, pharmacist or
            dentist, who is entitled to practise his or her profession in Hong Kong;
                (Added 6 of 2015 s. 3)

member (成員), in relation
            to the Board, means the Chairperson, an appointed member or an elected member;
                (Added 6 of 2015 s. 3)

qualified candidate (合資格候選人) means a registered veterinary surgeon who is qualified under the
            Election Regulation to stand for an election to elect an elected member;
                (Added 6 of 2015 s. 3)

register (名冊) means the
            register of registered veterinary surgeons established and maintained under section
                5(a);

veterinary service (獸醫服務) means doing or performing any act or attending to any matter the doing
            or performing of which or the attending to which forms part of the generally accepted
            practice of veterinary surgery;

paragraph.content:
(if the Chairperson is a registered veterinary surgeon) an order under
                            section 19 is in force in respect of the
                        Chairperson;

subparagraph.content:
has entered into a voluntary arrangement within the meaning of the
                            Bankruptcy Ordinance (Cap. 6) with his or her
                            creditors which is still in force;

paragraph.content:
(if the appointed member is a registered veterinary surgeon) an order
                        under section 19 is in force in respect of the appointed
                        member;

subparagraph.content:
has entered into a voluntary arrangement within the meaning of the
                            Bankruptcy Ordinance (Cap. 6) with his or her
                            creditors which is still in force;

has entered into a voluntary arrangement within the meaning of the
                            Bankruptcy Ordinance (Cap. 6) with his or her
                            creditors which is still in force;

has entered into a voluntary arrangement within the meaning of the
                            Bankruptcy Ordinance (Cap. 6) with his or her
                            creditors which is still in force;

paragraph.content:
applying medication or treatment (other than anaesthetic drugs) topically
                    or administering medication or treatment (other than anaesthetic drugs) orally,
                    per-rectally or by inhalation;

aiding the registered veterinary surgeon who is performing and is in charge
                    of a medical or surgical procedure, but not making any decision on the
                    procedure;

administering medication specific to the animal per-rectally, parenterally
                    or by inhalation under the direction of a registered veterinary
                    surgeon;
